1
00:01:33,040 --> 00:01:34,080
What’s the matter?

2
00:01:35,880 --> 00:01:37,600
I could ask you the same question.

3
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:39,400
You sighed first.

4
00:01:40,840 --> 00:01:42,480
I think I heard you sigh first.

5
00:01:42,600 --> 00:01:44,680
- I did not.
- You did too.

6
00:01:46,960 --> 00:01:49,760
Fine, I sighed first, so I won.
You go first.

7
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:56,720
Why am I arguing with you?

8
00:01:58,640 --> 00:02:02,960
- Don’t tell me…
- Stop your wild imagination, Rain.

9
00:02:03,520 --> 00:02:07,680
I didn’t fight with P’ Pai.
It’s P’ Pai and his family.

10
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:12,000
What happened?

11
00:02:13,480 --> 00:02:15,280
Tell me, I wanna hear it.

12
00:02:18,640 --> 00:02:20,520
You seem to be in a good mood today.

13
00:02:21,040 --> 00:02:25,720
Yes, I have a date tonight.
It’s rare for him to come see me here.

14
00:02:26,720 --> 00:02:29,360
Nong Sky?
Shall I go get him?

15
00:02:29,640 --> 00:02:32,680
It’s okay, he’ll call me when he arrives.

16
00:02:32,840 --> 00:02:36,080
You’re so cute, Nong Sky.
Let me give you a hug.

17
00:02:37,840 --> 00:02:38,960
P’ Plerng.

18
00:02:39,200 --> 00:02:41,840
- Come on, Sky.
- P’ Pai’s gonna see us.

19
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:44,880
Hey! How did you get here?

20
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:47,920
Why couldn’t I come?

21
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:51,040
This is Dad’s company,
which means it’s also mine.

22
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:54,360
And I’m the one who brought Sky up here.

23
00:02:55,720 --> 00:02:57,040
You’re so terrible, P’ Pai.

24
00:02:57,400 --> 00:02:59,360
How could you let him
wait on the first floor?

25
00:02:59,440 --> 00:03:00,520
It’s not what you think.

26
00:03:00,560 --> 00:03:04,360
I was about to call you
when P’ Plerng saw me.

27
00:03:04,840 --> 00:03:07,480
- So we came up together.
- Sky, don’t speak up for him.

28
00:03:08,320 --> 00:03:11,120
You can come to me if P’ Pai mistreats you.

29
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:13,440
That’s enough.

30
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:15,800
This is my boyfriend.
Stop hugging him!

31
00:03:16,880 --> 00:03:17,960
Only I can hug him.

32
00:03:19,840 --> 00:03:21,160
Stingy!

33
00:03:22,200 --> 00:03:26,360
Don’t listen to him.
If he invites you out, don’t go.

34
00:03:26,480 --> 00:03:31,320
Or if he buys you a gift, don’t accept it.
I’ll buy it for you.

35
00:03:31,520 --> 00:03:35,280
But Mom wants to meet Sky.
She’s already booked a restaurant.

36
00:03:35,920 --> 00:03:38,520
Sky, please don’t be mean to our mom.

37
00:03:38,640 --> 00:03:39,840
Don’t believe him.

38
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:44,240
How could she book a restaurant?
I haven’t told her that you’d come.

39
00:03:48,320 --> 00:03:49,320
What are you doing?

40
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:53,560
Telling Mom.
And now she knows.

41
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:02,040
Okay, let’s have dinner together tonight.

42
00:04:03,920 --> 00:04:06,960
Nong Sky, you should come this way
or you'll go crazy like them.

43
00:04:07,040 --> 00:04:08,600
- Who are you calling crazy?
- Who are you calling crazy?

44
00:04:11,920 --> 00:04:15,120
P’ Tan, is it alright to let them be?

45
00:04:15,480 --> 00:04:20,120
Don’t worry, everyone’s just teasing
Mr. Pai and showing you affection.

46
00:04:20,560 --> 00:04:23,600
We should get out of here.
Come on, let’s go.

47
00:04:24,200 --> 00:04:25,280
Let’s go outside.

48
00:04:30,480 --> 00:04:32,440
How could you do this?
He’s my boyfriend.

49
00:04:32,560 --> 00:04:34,960
Who told you to make him wait downstairs?

50
00:04:35,080 --> 00:04:38,320
I didn’t make him wait.
Sky was about to call me. You heard him.

51
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:43,240
So P’ Pai’s whole family likes you.

52
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:50,360
And P’ Pai, his parents, and
siblings are waging war to snatch you.

53
00:04:51,720 --> 00:04:54,680
Wow, my friend's become
their favorite son-in-law.

54
00:04:57,720 --> 00:05:02,320
I don’t know if I’m their favorite,
but I don’t want to upset any of them.

55
00:05:03,360 --> 00:05:06,720
‘Cause I want his family to like me.

56
00:05:10,520 --> 00:05:12,560
What about you?
Why did you follow me here?

57
00:05:14,760 --> 00:05:16,000
I’m lonely.

58
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:18,520
And it’s summer break.
I’ve got nothing to do.

59
00:05:19,120 --> 00:05:21,800
Don’t tell me you fought with P’ Payu.

60
00:05:23,080 --> 00:05:25,960
No, I didn’t fight with P’ Payu.

61
00:05:28,520 --> 00:05:32,120
I’m just annoyed that he’s attractive.

62
00:05:36,360 --> 00:05:38,840
I think it’s okay.
What do you think?

63
00:05:39,520 --> 00:05:41,600
- Let’s adjust it a bit.
- How?

64
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:50,800
Perfect.

65
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:54,440
- Not yet.
- What’s missing?

66
00:05:55,320 --> 00:05:56,520
Turn around.

67
00:05:58,720 --> 00:06:01,520
Yeah, this is it.
That’s what I’m talking about.

68
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:02,720
- Fuck you.
- Perfect.

69
00:06:05,280 --> 00:06:07,200
Why do I have to wear this costume, Sig?

70
00:06:07,880 --> 00:06:11,200
‘Cause our faculty will be putting
on a Korean historical play this year.

71
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:15,280
And you look the most
like an ancient Korean.

72
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:20,280
It’s okay if you’re not gonna perform,
but you must be our mannequin.

73
00:06:20,720 --> 00:06:21,760
Okay?

74
00:06:25,840 --> 00:06:28,360
Just do us a favor.

75
00:06:28,360 --> 00:06:31,000
The guy who’s supposed to be
at the fitting got food poisoning.

76
00:06:31,040 --> 00:06:34,120
And both of you’ve got similar body sizes.
See? It’s a fit.

77
00:06:34,160 --> 00:06:35,160
He’s right.

78
00:06:37,400 --> 00:06:40,960
I wouldn’t have worn it
if it hadn’t been for your sake.

79
00:06:41,120 --> 00:06:44,040
Hold on, why Sky’s sake?

80
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:46,600
Why can’t you do it for my sake?
What’s wrong with me?

81
00:06:48,040 --> 00:06:49,720
It’s because I don’t like you.

82
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:51,320
- Got it?
- Here we go again.

83
00:06:51,360 --> 00:06:53,840
Very well, very well.

84
00:06:53,960 --> 00:06:57,560
You’ve gotten arrogant
after getting yourself a hubby.

85
00:06:58,600 --> 00:06:59,720
Don’t mock me.

86
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:02,400
- ‘It’s because I don’t like you.’
- What’s wrong with you?

87
00:07:02,440 --> 00:07:04,920
Look at this, everyone!

88
00:07:21,840 --> 00:07:25,280
Well? Doesn’t he look stunning?
It’s done by me.

89
00:07:25,920 --> 00:07:28,800
Why is P’ Payu wearing this costume?
And why are you with Ple?

90
00:07:28,840 --> 00:07:33,080
Hey, it’s not what you think.
I don’t have feelings for him anymore.

91
00:07:33,520 --> 00:07:37,400
When I was picking up the altered
costume, I met P’ Payu on the way.

92
00:07:37,960 --> 00:07:41,440
You know our lead actor
can’t come to the fitting.

93
00:07:41,520 --> 00:07:44,640
So I asked P’ Payu to try it on instead.

94
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:46,400
Well? What do you think?

95
00:07:46,400 --> 00:07:47,720
He looks great!

96
00:07:47,720 --> 00:07:50,240
So much better than Rain.
Sawasdee krub.

97
00:07:50,480 --> 00:07:52,520
- P’ Payu in this costume…
- What?

98
00:07:52,560 --> 00:07:54,080
I won’t let you look at him anymore.

99
00:07:54,440 --> 00:07:56,920
- Huh?
- Enough. Stop looking. Stop watching.

100
00:07:57,680 --> 00:07:59,000
- I’m gonna look.
- No.

101
00:07:59,040 --> 00:08:02,120
Since you’re here, can I take
a photo with you, P’ Payu?

102
00:08:02,120 --> 00:08:03,120
- Take a photo for me.
- Hurry up.

103
00:08:03,120 --> 00:08:05,080
- I’d be greatly honored.
- No, I won’t let you.

104
00:08:05,080 --> 00:08:07,200
- P’ Payu’s a star now.
- Hey!

105
00:08:07,240 --> 00:08:08,640
- I want a photo too.
- Don't...

106
00:08:08,640 --> 00:08:09,960
Come here.
Get away from him.

107
00:08:10,520 --> 00:08:12,640
- No photos.
- Say cheese.

108
00:08:12,840 --> 00:08:15,280
- No.
- Do the cyclone pose.

109
00:08:15,720 --> 00:08:16,880
Come with me right now!

110
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:25,600
Why are you looking at me like that?
It doesn’t suit me?

111
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:28,760
Yeah, it doesn’t.
It doesn’t suit you very much.

112
00:08:28,760 --> 00:08:31,280
- Take it off right now.
- It really doesn’t suit me?

113
00:08:34,320 --> 00:08:37,600
Well… It does.

114
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:45,160
Of course, you like to see me cosplay.
So how could you not like it?

115
00:08:45,320 --> 00:08:47,080
I don’t like to see you cosplay.

116
00:08:47,240 --> 00:08:52,680
But you sometimes want me to
put on a racing suit or a pilot uniform.

117
00:08:56,400 --> 00:08:57,480
It’s because...

118
00:08:59,320 --> 00:09:04,120
My boyfriend’s handsome.
He looks good in everything.

119
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:06,800
Don’t change the subject.

120
00:09:07,400 --> 00:09:09,440
You were bullying me.
I saw it.

121
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:11,280
What did I do?

122
00:09:12,080 --> 00:09:15,280
Everyone was bullying me.
You were supposed to take my side.

123
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:19,880
How could you let Sig take a photo?
And I saw you put your arm around Sky.

124
00:09:22,160 --> 00:09:24,080
My boyfriend’s gotten smarter.

125
00:09:26,560 --> 00:09:27,960
You’re calling me stupid again.

126
00:09:33,680 --> 00:09:36,320
‘Stupid’ means ‘cute.’

127
00:09:43,920 --> 00:09:45,480
Actually…

128
00:09:47,240 --> 00:09:49,680
Actually?

129
00:09:52,920 --> 00:09:55,920
You look handsome in this costume.
I wanna keep you to myself.

130
00:10:03,600 --> 00:10:05,120
I think so too.

131
00:10:05,880 --> 00:10:08,520
You should only wear this
costume when you’re alone with me.

132
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:14,640
And if you don’t take it off soon,
I’m gonna walk around in this costume.

133
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:17,920
Hey, hold on! I’m taking it off.
I’m taking it off right now.

134
00:10:18,160 --> 00:10:21,600
But you must take it off too.
Come here, come take it off with me.

135
00:10:27,680 --> 00:10:31,080
You’re upset ‘cause the juniors were
fangirling over P’ Payu in costume?

136
00:10:31,520 --> 00:10:32,760
My friend’s so childish!

137
00:10:33,720 --> 00:10:36,080
You’ve really got no idea, Sky.

138
00:10:36,120 --> 00:10:37,920
His photos were spread
to accountancy faculty.

139
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:40,400
That buliding's miles away from ours.

140
00:10:40,840 --> 00:10:42,560
And he’s got a lot more followers now.

141
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:45,520
So this is why you’re sulking?

142
00:10:46,040 --> 00:10:49,480
That’s why I said you’re childish.
P’ Payu didn't do anything wrong.

143
00:10:50,160 --> 00:10:54,640
The hell he didn’t.
He laughed every time I brought it up.

144
00:10:55,120 --> 00:10:56,200
It’s so frustrating.

145
00:10:58,200 --> 00:11:02,520
Maybe he likes seeing you huff and puff?
I think it’s funny.

146
00:11:03,880 --> 00:11:04,960
Sky!

147
00:11:05,720 --> 00:11:09,120
What?
Hey, is that all of your story?

148
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:12,000
Huh?

149
00:11:13,720 --> 00:11:14,720
No.

150
00:11:15,920 --> 00:11:18,920
Have you ever called P’ Pai ‘Daddy’?

151
00:11:20,040 --> 00:11:21,040
What?

152
00:11:23,440 --> 00:11:25,200
Have you ever called P’ Pai ‘Daddy’?

153
00:11:25,720 --> 00:11:26,800
What did you say?

154
00:11:28,160 --> 00:11:31,400
Have you ever called P’ Pai ‘Daddy’!
Daddy!

155
00:11:33,240 --> 00:11:35,120
- Daddy?
- Yeah.

156
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:42,200
Daddy.

157
00:11:52,640 --> 00:11:53,640
What's this?

158
00:11:54,320 --> 00:11:56,720
A book.
What do you think it is?

159
00:11:58,960 --> 00:12:02,720
I know it’s a book,
but why are you giving it to me?

160
00:12:03,720 --> 00:12:07,720
A book is for reading
and I want you to read it.

161
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:10,560
How many days have you been lazing around?

162
00:12:11,080 --> 00:12:14,240
I promised your mama to push you hard.

163
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:20,040
Get up and do something else.
Don’t just play with your phone.

164
00:12:24,280 --> 00:12:27,600
You’re acting like a dad, P’ Payu.

165
00:12:35,560 --> 00:12:37,360
Who did you call dad?

166
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:45,640
You.

167
00:12:46,600 --> 00:12:50,720
Papa, Dad, Daddy.

168
00:12:55,880 --> 00:12:59,800
Then I’d better teach
the difference between...

169
00:13:01,480 --> 00:13:03,360
'Daddy'...

170
00:13:05,320 --> 00:13:07,000
And 'hubby'...

171
00:13:09,480 --> 00:13:10,840
To you.

172
00:13:24,880 --> 00:13:26,200
Enough already, P’ Payu.

173
00:13:38,480 --> 00:13:45,280
I’m making sure you know
the difference between ‘daddy’ and ‘hubby’.

174
00:13:47,360 --> 00:13:48,680
I already know it.

175
00:13:50,720 --> 00:13:53,160
My papa doesn’t squeeze my chest like this.

176
00:13:57,040 --> 00:13:58,680
Ouch! Don’t pinch!

177
00:14:05,880 --> 00:14:06,920
You know what?

178
00:14:08,040 --> 00:14:09,480
When I teach...

179
00:14:12,560 --> 00:14:14,360
I teach to the core.

180
00:14:29,160 --> 00:14:30,880
What did you call me again?

181
00:14:36,600 --> 00:14:37,600
Daddy.

182
00:15:07,800 --> 00:15:13,160
Are you sure you wanna call me daddy?

183
00:15:34,280 --> 00:15:35,800
P’ Payu, please hear me out.

184
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:42,960
By my definition, ‘daddy’ isn’t a father.

185
00:15:46,080 --> 00:15:50,080
To me, ‘daddy’ means…

186
00:15:53,880 --> 00:15:55,080
Hubby.

187
00:16:11,680 --> 00:16:12,720
Daddy.

188
00:16:14,480 --> 00:16:15,480
Hubby.

189
00:16:18,160 --> 00:16:19,200
Daddy.

190
00:16:20,880 --> 00:16:21,880
Daddy.

191
00:16:29,440 --> 00:16:31,360
I told you it’s nothing.

192
00:16:32,880 --> 00:16:35,440
Okay, if you say so.

193
00:16:45,400 --> 00:16:47,800
Sky! You!

194
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:49,720
Your face says it all, Rain.

195
00:16:49,760 --> 00:16:52,000
P’ Payu must’ve done
something that made you shy.

196
00:16:52,080 --> 00:16:54,200
But it’s fine if you don’t wanna tell me.

197
00:16:55,120 --> 00:16:58,440
Sky, get in the pool now.
Get in.

198
00:16:58,480 --> 00:16:59,520
No way.

199
00:17:02,080 --> 00:17:04,840
By the way, didn’t you say
you’d go on a trip with P’ Payu?

200
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:10,240
He’s busy.
Do you wanna go with me?

201
00:17:12,720 --> 00:17:16,560
No.
I just went to Lopburi with P’ Pai.

202
00:17:16,760 --> 00:17:19,160
And I’ve got to prepare
the orientation activities.

203
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:21,280
I’m up to my eyes in work.

204
00:17:22,080 --> 00:17:26,280
Oh, so you took him to Lopburi.

205
00:17:26,760 --> 00:17:29,560
To pay respect to your father, P’ Sky?

206
00:17:31,160 --> 00:17:32,600
Will you stop being nosy for once?

207
00:17:34,320 --> 00:17:36,320
You make me even more curious now.

208
00:17:38,600 --> 00:17:40,080
Let’s have a heart-to-heart.

209
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:45,720
What is P’ Pai’s size?

210
00:17:48,920 --> 00:17:51,120
What size are you talking about?
I don’t know anything.

211
00:17:51,360 --> 00:17:52,880
Don’t play dumb.

212
00:17:53,520 --> 00:17:55,120
- Come on, tell me.
- No.

213
00:17:55,160 --> 00:17:56,480
- Tell me.
- I won’t tell you. No.

214
00:17:56,520 --> 00:17:58,160
- Come on.
- No, no. I won’t tell you.

215
00:17:58,160 --> 00:18:01,280
Don’t you follow me!
Rain! Don’t. Don’t.

216
00:18:01,280 --> 00:18:02,560
- Go away.
- Why are you shy?

217
00:18:02,600 --> 00:18:04,200
- I’m not shy.
- Your face's red.

218
00:18:04,240 --> 00:18:05,920
- It's not.
- It's redder than that building’s lights.

219
00:18:05,960 --> 00:18:07,720
- Stop exaggerating.
- I’m not.

220
00:18:07,760 --> 00:18:08,920
I'm not exaggerating.

221
00:18:12,960 --> 00:18:15,880
You bought quite a lot.
Let me help you.

222
00:18:16,880 --> 00:18:20,400
You said you’d be working late,
so I was afraid you might be hungry.

223
00:18:22,440 --> 00:18:24,000
Then can I eat something else too?

224
00:18:25,600 --> 00:18:26,800
Have you finished your work?

225
00:18:27,280 --> 00:18:29,960
No, I’ve got a meeting
with the Europe branch.

226
00:18:33,400 --> 00:18:38,480
Next time, tell me when you
work hard so that I’ll come see you.

227
00:18:41,240 --> 00:18:42,880
This is enough to recharge me.

228
00:18:45,760 --> 00:18:48,560
Now that I’m recharged,
I’m gonna wrap up my work.

229
00:18:48,880 --> 00:18:50,120
And we’ll ‘eat’ after that.

230
00:18:52,760 --> 00:18:54,200
I know what you’re thinking.

231
00:18:54,880 --> 00:18:55,960
Come on, let’s go.

232
00:19:23,440 --> 00:19:24,640
I’ve finished my work.

233
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:30,320
Give me a second, P’ Pai.
I’m in the middle of the game.

234
00:19:30,360 --> 00:19:31,400
I don’t wanna lose.

235
00:19:31,760 --> 00:19:33,280
But I already finished my work.

236
00:19:33,800 --> 00:19:37,040
Besides, Plerng and Phan
aren’t here to disturb us today.

237
00:19:40,560 --> 00:19:42,880
Just a sec, let me play the game first.

238
00:19:56,120 --> 00:19:57,800
I told you to give me a second.

239
00:19:59,640 --> 00:20:03,160
Keep playing your game.
I’m gonna play mine.

240
00:20:10,800 --> 00:20:14,880
- Is this how you wanna play it?
- Yes, I’m gonna play it like this.

241
00:21:01,120 --> 00:21:02,280
Lift your ass.

